Genitalia (
Fig. 8
). Epiphallus as long as penis. Vas deferens entering penial sheath halfway up. Penis five times longer than wide, not coiled inside sheath, inner penial wall with weak, irregular longitudinal pilasters restricted to anterior half, posteriorly with thick, cone-shaped pad. Vagina half as long as penis, a third of length of free oviduct, bursa copulatrix with elongated, pointed well-differentiated end.
